race.comment: DAMEHOOD (2) looked a run short at Caulfield first up in stronger. The gate is handy enough and Ethan Brown sticks and he's flying. The narrow defeat two back on the Lakeside reads well. KOKAKO (5) resumes with winning rider Jamie Melham in the saddle. Won this grade fresh at Bendigo two back and pulled up with an issue following. Has a soft draw and her Cranbourne jumpouts have been sharp. MIGLIORARE (6) disappointed second-up but led and won a Cranbourne Maiden easily prior. The tongue tie is applied for the first time and quick improvement is likely. ALLINTHETIMING (1) won well fresh at Mt Gambier over 1212m. Goes well second up and have to respect the ease of that win but this is tougher.
